  $S$Best matched Hospitals for ENT in the UAE - Allocation Assist$S$,
  $BT$Hi Dr. {{doctor_name}},

I hope you are doing well.

From our experience in the market, below are the hospitals that we feel are most relevant and suitable for your speciality and training. We have recommended your profile to these hospitals. Please see the information guide provided for each hospital to find out more about their facilities.

For an ENT, the most appropriate hospitals are those with specialized ENT departments such as:
In Dubai:
American Hospital - Known for its high-quality healthcare services and specialized ENT departments.
Al Zahra Hospital - Recognized for its strong ENT department with high volumes of ear, nose, and throat procedures and modern infrastructure.
Clemenceau Hospital - Recognized for its advanced medical facilities and specialized ENT services.
King's College Hospital - Associated with its UK parent hospital, it offers specialized ENT surgeries, including aviation-related cases.
Rashid Hospital - A major government hospital with comprehensive ENT services and specialists.
Saudi German Hospital - Has multiple ENT surgeons in Al Barsha area and good track record on sinus surgeries.
NMC Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Well-known in the UAE for providing comprehensive healthcare services, including ENT.
Mediclinic Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Has specialized ENT clinics and experienced ENT surgeons.
In Abu Dhabi:
Sheikh Shakhbout Medical City - A major government hospital with comprehensive ENT services.
Sheikh Khalifa Medical City - One of the leading government hospitals in the UAE and is highly regarded for its comprehensive healthcare services, including ENT (Ear, Nose and Throat) care.
Burjeel Medical Group (Burjeel Medical City, Burjeel Abu Dhabi & Burjeel Al Ain) - Renowned private hospital with specialized ENT clinics.
In Sharjah and Fujairah:
Sharjah University Hospital - Provides ENT services as part of its comprehensive care.
Al Sharq Hospital (Fujairah) - Offers ENT services locally.

However the UAE is a very progressive country with a rapidly evolving healthcare sector and sometimes the hospitals have unannounced plans to build departments, so we also recommend introducing our Doctors' profiles to other leading hospitals in case they have plans in the future.

