  $S$Best matched Hospitals for General Surgeon in the UAE - Allocation Assist$S$,
  $BT$Hi Dr. {{doctor_name}},

I hope you are doing well.

From our experience in the market, below are the hospitals that we feel are most relevant and suitable for your speciality and training. We have recommended your profile to these hospitals. Please see the information guide provided for each hospital to find out more about their facilities.

For a General Surgeon, the most appropriate hospitals are those with specialized General Surgery departments such as:
In Dubai:
American Hospital - Known for excellent healthcare standards and specialized surgical services.
Al Zahra Hospital - Private, JCI-accredited, well known for general and laparoscopic surgery, with personalized patient care and respected international-standard teams.
Fakeeh University Hospital - Private, JCI-accredited, globally recognized (Newsweek/Statista 5‑star rating), combining clinical excellence with modern education infrastructure. Offers general surgery among other specialties.
King's College Hospital - JCI-accredited branch of London’s King’s College Hospital. Offers general surgery as part of a broader multi-specialty portfolio.
NMC Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - JCI accredited and offering general surgery as part of a wide portfolio including orthopedics and cardiology. Known for accessibility and consistent quality across the network.
Rashid Hospital - A major government hospital with extensive surgical departments and high patient volume.
Saudi German Hospital - JCI-accredited network, known for robotic-assisted surgeries and high success rates in general surgical procedures, especially orthopedics and oncology but also general surgery
Mediclinic Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Part of a reputable international healthcare group with strong surgical services.
In Abu Dhabi:
Sheikh Shakhbout Medical City - A leading government hospital with advanced surgical facilities.
Sheikh Khalifa Medical City - Known for specialized and general surgical procedures.
Burjeel Medical Group (Burjeel Medical City, Burjeel Abu Dhabi & Burjeel Al Ain) - High-end private network with expertise in minimally invasive, robotic, bariatric, endocrine, hepatobiliary, and transplant-related general surgery services. JCI-accredited with a reputation for surgical precision and patient-centered care.
Mubadala Group - Renowned for high-quality surgical care.
In Sharjah and Fujairah:
Sharjah University Hospital - Reputable academic hospital with surgical departments.
Al Sharq Hospital (Fujairah) - Known for general healthcare, including surgery.

However the UAE is a very progressive country with a rapidly evolving healthcare sector and sometimes the hospitals have unannounced plans to build departments, so we also recommend introducing our Doctors' profiles to other leading hospitals in case they have plans in the future.

