  'profile_sent',
  $S$Best matched Hospitals for Medical Oncologist in the UAE - Allocation Assist$S$,
  $BT$Hi Dr. {{doctor_name}},

I hope you are doing well.

From our experience in the market, below are the hospitals that we feel are most relevant and suitable for your speciality and training. We have recommended your profile to these hospitals. Please see the information guide provided for each hospital to find out more about their facilities.

For a Medical Oncologist, the most appropriate hospitals are those with specialized Medical Oncology departments such as:
In Dubai:
American Hospital - Known for advanced cancer treatment, multidisciplinary oncology teams, and international standards.
Mediclinic Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Provides specialized oncology services with multidisciplinary teams.
DHA Hospitals (Dubai Hospital & Rashid Hospital) - A major public hospitals with oncology services, including chemotherapy, radiotherapy, and surgical oncology.
Clemenceau Hospital - Part of Johns Hopkins Medicine International, offering advanced cancer treatments.
King's College Hospital - The hospital offers a full spectrum of cancer care: diagnosis, treatment of solid tumors and hematologic cancers, immunotherapy, monoclonal antibodies, hormonal therapies, management of side effects, palliative care, survivorship programs.
NMC Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Well established healthcare providers in the UAE, known for offering a wide range of medical services, including oncology.
In Abu Dhabi:
Sheikh Shakhbout Medical City – A leading tertiary hospital with comprehensive oncology services, including chemotherapy, radiotherapy, and surgical options.
Sheikh Khalifa Medical City - Offers extensive cancer care with multidisciplinary oncology teams.
Burjeel Medical Group (Burjeel Medical City, Burjeel Abu Dhabi & Burjeel Al Ain) - Known for high-quality healthcare, including oncology services.
Mubadala Group - Collaborates with specialized hospitals and clinics that may offer oncology services.
In Sharjah and Fujairah:
Sharjah University Hospital - Provides oncology services, part of the University of Sharjah Health Sciences.
Al Sharq Hospital (Fujairah) - Offers cancer treatment and oncology services.

However the UAE is a very progressive country with a rapidly evolving healthcare sector and sometimes the hospitals have unannounced plans to build departments, so we also recommend introducing our Doctors' profiles to other leading hospitals in case they have plans in the future.

