  $S$Best matched Hospitals for Medical Genetics in the UAE - Allocation Assist$S$,
  $BT$Hi Dr. {{doctor_name}},

I hope you are doing well.

From our experience in the market, below are the hospitals that we feel are most relevant and suitable for your speciality and training. We have recommended your profile to these hospitals. Please see the information guide provided for each hospital to find out more about their facilities.

For a Medical Genetics, the most appropriate hospitals are those with specialized Medical Genetics departments such as:
In Dubai:
American Hospital - Known for comprehensive medical services and advanced diagnostics.
King's College Hospital - Offers a range of specialized services, and its affiliation with a leading UK institution suggests a high standard of care and access to advanced diagnostics.
Rashid Hospital - A major government hospital with extensive specialties, including genetics and pediatrics.
NMC Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Provides comprehensive healthcare services, including genetic testing and counseling, particularly for pediatric and adult genetic disorders. They often collaborate with specialized laboratories for genetic testing.
Mediclinic Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Part of Mediclinic International, offering specialized services and genetic counseling.
In Abu Dhabi:
Sheikh Shakhbout Medical City - Large government hospital with multidisciplinary services, likely including genetics.
Sheikh Khalifa Medical City - One of the leading healthcare institutions with comprehensive specialties.
Burjeel Medical City - Private hospital with advanced diagnostics and specialties.
Tawam Hospital - Known for maternal and pediatric care, potentially offering genetics services.
In Sharjah and Fujairah:
Sharjah University Hospital - Academic hospital with potential genetics services.
Al Sharq Hospital (Fujairah) - Offers general medical services; suitability for genetics depends on specific needs.

However the UAE is a very progressive country with a rapidly evolving healthcare sector and sometimes the hospitals have unannounced plans to build departments, so we also recommend introducing our Doctors' profiles to other leading hospitals in case they have plans in the future.

