insert into public.email_templates (key, name, flow_key, subject, body_text, body_html, variables, updated_at) values (
  $K$doctor_bmh_pulmonologist$K$,
  $N$Doctor · Best matched · Pulmonologist$N$,
  'profile_sent',
  $S$Best matched Hospitals for Pulmonologist in the UAE - Allocation Assist$S$,
  $BT$Hi Dr. {{doctor_name}},

I hope you are doing well.

From our experience in the market, below are the hospitals that we feel are most relevant and suitable for your speciality and training. We have recommended your profile to these hospitals. Please see the information guide provided for each hospital to find out more about their facilities.

For a Pulmonologist, the most appropriate hospitals are those with specialized Pulmonology departments such as:
In Dubai:
American Hospital - Known for comprehensive respiratory care, advanced diagnostics, and internationally trained specialists.
Al Zahra Hospital - Has comprehensive respiratory diagnostic and treatment services with experienced pulmonologists and respiratory specialists.
Rashid Hospital - A major government hospital with specialized respiratory and pulmonary units, serving a large patient population.
King's College Hospital - A reputable and well-established healthcare facility known for its high standards of care and specialization in various medical fields, including respiratory and pulmonology services.
Mediclinic Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Known for quality respiratory care and pulmonology specialists.
Fakeeh University Hospital - Offers modern diagnostic tools and respiratory treatments with experienced pulmonologists and healthcare professionals.
Saudi German Hospital - Provides a range of respiratory services, including bronchoscopy, pulmonary rehabilitation and chronic respiratory disease management.
NMC Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Well known healthcare providers in the UAE, offering a range of medical specialties, including pulmonology.
In Abu Dhabi:
Sheikh Shakhbout Medical City - A leading hospital with advanced pulmonology and respiratory care services.
Sheikh Khalifa Medical City - It is a major tertiary care hospital with advanced medical technology and highly trained specialists across various disciplines, including pulmonology.
Burjeel Medical Group (Burjeel Medical City, Burjeel Abu Dhabi & Burjeel Al Ain) - Offers specialized pulmonology departments with state-of-the-art facilities.
Mubadala Group - Known for high-quality healthcare services, including pulmonology.
In Sharjah and Fujairah:
Sharjah University Hospital - Offers pulmonology services and respiratory care.

However the UAE is a very progressive country with a rapidly evolving healthcare sector and sometimes the hospitals have unannounced plans to build departments, so we also recommend introducing our Doctors' profiles to other leading hospitals in case they have plans in the future.

Here is an entire list of our hospital network in the UAE:

