  'profile_sent',
  $S$Best matched Hospitals for Rheumatologist in the UAE - Allocation Assist$S$,
  $BT$Hi Dr. {{doctor_name}},

I hope you are doing well.

From our experience in the market, below are the hospitals that we feel are most relevant and suitable for your speciality and training. We have recommended your profile to these hospitals. Please see the information guide provided for each hospital to find out more about their facilities.

For a Rheumatologist, the most appropriate hospitals are those with specialized Rheumatology departments such as:
In Dubai:
Rashid Hospital - A major public hospital that offers rheumatology services.
Dubai Hospital (Dubai Health Authority) - Public tertiary center with a dedicated rheumatology department as part of DHA facilities, including Dubai, Rashid, Latifa Hospitals.
King's College Hospital - As a leading hospital in the UK and internationally, King's College Hospital has a strong reputation for its rheumatology department, which is part of its renowned Rheumatology and Immunology service.
NMC Hospitals (Dubai and Abu Dhabi) - offers a wide range of specialities including rheumatology.
Mediclinic Hospitals (Dubai and Abu Dhabi) - offers comprehensive rheumatology services for conditions like RA, lupus, vasculitis, osteoporosis, gout, etc.
In Abu Dhabi:
Sheikh Shakhbout Medical City - A major hospital that offers comprehensive rheumatology services.
Sheikh Khalifa Medical City - A well-established and highly reputable healthcare facility with a broad range of specialties, including rheumatology.
Reem Hospital - A new hospital that offers rheumatology services.
Burjeel Medical Group (Burjeel Medical City, Burjeel Abu Dhabi & Burjeel Al Ain) - A major hospital that offers rheumatology services.
Tawam Hospital - Affiliated with Johns Hopkins Medicine and JCI accredited, serving as a regional referral center in Abu Dhabi with a dedicated rheumatology service and pediatric/adult coverage.

However the UAE is a very progressive country with a rapidly evolving healthcare sector and sometimes the hospitals have unannounced plans to build departments, so we also recommend introducing our Doctors' profiles to other leading hospitals in case they have plans in the future.

