  $BT$Hi Dr. {{doctor_name}},

I hope you are doing well.

From our experience in the market, below are the hospitals that we feel are most relevant and suitable for your speciality and training. We have recommended your profile to these hospitals. Please see the information guide provided for each hospital to find out more about their facilities.

For a Visceral Surgeon, the most appropriate hospitals are those with specialized Visceral Surgery departments such as:
In Dubai:
American Hospital - Known for advanced surgical services and experienced specialists.
Al Zahra Hospital - Recognized for surgical specialties, including visceral procedures.
King's College Hospital - An extension of the renowned UK hospital, with advanced surgical options.
Fakeeh University Hospital - Known for advanced medical services, including surgery.
NMC Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - They offer general and specialized surgical procedures, including visceral surgeries such as gastrointestinal, liver, pancreatic and other abdominal surgeries. Their surgeons are trained and experienced in these areas.
Rashid Hospital - A major public hospital with extensive surgical departments.
Mediclinic Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Part of a reputable healthcare group with specialized surgical services.
In Abu Dhabi:
Sheikh Shakhbout Medical City - A leading government hospital with comprehensive surgical departments.
Sheikh Khalifa Medical City - A major hospital with surgical services.
Burjeel Medical Group (Burjeel Medical City, Burjeel Abu Dhabi & Burjeel Al Ain) - Relevant and reputable choices for visceral surgery in the UAE. They are equipped with experienced surgeons and modern facilities suitable for such procedures.
In Sharjah and Fujairah:
Sharjah University Hospital - A relevant and competent facility for visceral surgery, especially for routine cases and those suitable for a teaching hospital environment.
Al Sharq Hospital (Fujairah) - Relevant and capable for general and routine visceral surgeries, especially within the Fujairah region.

However the UAE is a very progressive country with a rapidly evolving healthcare sector and sometimes the hospitals have unannounced plans to build departments, so we also recommend introducing our Doctors' profiles to other leading hospitals in case they have plans in the future.

Here is an entire list of our hospital network in the UAE:

