  $BT$Hi Dr. {{doctor_name}},

I hope you are doing well.

From our experience in the market, below are the hospitals that we feel are most relevant and suitable for your speciality and training. We have recommended your profile to these hospitals. Please see the information guide provided for each hospital to find out more about their facilities.

For an Orthopedic Surgeon, the most appropriate hospitals are those with specialized Orthopedic Surgery departments such as:
In Dubai:
American Hospital - Known for advanced orthopedic services and international standards of care.
Al Zahra Hospital - Known for minimally invasive surgery, modern diagnostics, and good patient care in orthopedics.
Clemenceau Hospital - Offers orthopedic care with modern facilities.
Fakeeh University Hospital - Known for blending academic research with care delivery—suggesting adoption of innovative techniques including in orthopedics.
King's College Hospital - Emphasizes orthopedic care mixed with UK-standard protocols, especially for trauma and joint surgery.
NMC Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Their orthopedic departments offer comprehensive services: sports injuries, joint replacements, spine surgery, trauma, and pediatric orthopedics.
Rashid Hospital - A major public hospital with comprehensive orthopedic services.
Saudi German Hospital - Offers comprehensive orthopedic services and is frequently featured in national rankings.
Mediclinic Hospitals (Dubai & Abu Dhabi) - Part of the well-known private healthcare group with specialized orthopedic departments.
In Abu Dhabi:
Sheikh Shakhbout Medical City - A leading public hospital with comprehensive orthopedic services.
Sheikh Khalifa Medical City - Provides advanced orthopedic interventions.
Burjeel Medical Group (Burjeel Medical City, Burjeel Abu Dhabi & Burjeel Al Ain) - Renowned for orthopedic and joint replacement surgeries.
Tarmeem Hospital - Known for providing a range of medical services, including specialties like orthopedic surgery.
Tawam Hospital - Known for orthopedic surgery capabilities.

However the UAE is a very progressive country with a rapidly evolving healthcare sector and sometimes the hospitals have unannounced plans to build departments, so we also recommend introducing our Doctors' profiles to other leading hospitals in case they have plans in the future.

